# Versioning

All the repositories and deliverables will be using semantic versioning to maintain the versions of the system.

> Given a version number MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH, increment the:
> 
> - MAJOR version when you make incompatible API changes,
> - MINOR version when you add functionality in a backwards compatible manner, and
> - PATCH version when you make backwards compatible bug fixes.


Eg : 0.0.1

## Git Tagging Policy

### Versions

Everytime a version is increased, we will be adding a tag to all the git repositories involved with the new tag. And the version tag will be as the following format.

> {Version}
> Eg : 0.0.1

# Automation

Github Actions will be used for CI procedures due to tight integration with currently used tools. Any scripts or tool usage should be implemented in a way which can easily migrated to another setup.
